A look at LeBron James’ pursuit of Kareem Abdul-Jabbar for the NBA’s scoring record. Abdul-Jabbar has held the record since April 5, 1984:Abdul-Jabbar points: 38,387.James points: 38,104.Difference: 283 points.James’ latest game: He scored 32 points Wednesday in the Los Angeles Lakers’ 116-111 loss to Sacramento.James’ scoring average this season: 29.8.Potential record-breaker: At his current rate of 29.8 points per game, with 284 points needed to pass Abdul-Jabbar, it would take James 10 more games to become the NBA’s scoring leader. Assuming he does not miss any games, that makes the potential record-breaking game Feb. 7 at home against Oklahoma City.Next Lakers game: Friday at home against Memphis.___AP NBA: https://apnews.com/hub/NBA and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports